article.headline: Montana St. 77, San Jose St. 70
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Jamie Stewart scored 21 points and Christian Moon added 19 off the bench to lift Montana State to a 77-70 victory over San Jose State on Monday night. Stewart shot 4 for 8 from the field, including 3 of 4 from 3-point range, and sank 10 of 11 free throws for the Bobcats (3-3), who snapped a two-game losing streak. Moon made five 3-pointers. James Kinney scored 24 points for the Spartans (2-4), and Wil Carter had 15 points and eight rebounds. Jourdain Allou had 10 points and five rebounds for Montana State, which shot 45.8 percent (11 of 24) from 3-point range.
